  {
    "hotel_id": "1723671",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/apa-hotel-namba-eki-higashi/hotel/osaka-jp.html",
    "name": "APA Hotel Namba-Eki Higashi",
    "detail": "Space in Japan is limited. We've upgraded to a regular double room throughout our trip to have some more walking space considering our luggage and this was the only APA hotel that actually gave us a slightly larger room. It was also the cleanest - at the same time, it is also the newest out of all the APA hotels we stayed at. Location-wise, it is two stops from the main Umeda station where all the trains are available including the JR. However, it is in the middle of all the markets, foods, bars, and everyday activities. It's a few blocks away from Dontonbori, the Kuromon Ichiba Market, Shinsaibashisuji shopping street, animate osaka nipponbashi, and the train station which is a large mall itself. It's also two blocks from a Don Quijote. Staff were also extremely nice and helpful during our stay. When it came to directions, taxi services, housekeeping, etc. Highly recommend this APA hotel for the cleanliness, the accommodations, and the location, location, location. ",
